1. [/users/signup](http://localhost:8000/users/signup)  : Signup : POST

This is a POST request which inserts records into database in Users table.

This  method also searches if the user is already existing .If the user already exists it returns a message that already an user exists with a given email id

Upon success the counter value is incremented which is a four digit value and inserted into the database

Encryption : In order to store password in database and to provide security we are using encryption and decryption algorithms so passwords remain hidden

1. [users/login](http://localhost:8000/users/login)     : Login    : POST

This is a POST method which tests for user name and password and redirects to the gator meetup page upon login

 ![](data:image/*;base64,)

It also checks weather the user is registered user or not



 ![](data:image/*;base64,)

API used

In order to transport the password securely from the forms  to backend  Jsonwebtoken for auth token  is being used

JSON Web Token (JWT) is an open standard (RFC 7519) that defines a compact and self-contained way for securely transmitting information between parties as a JSON object. This information can be verified and trusted because it is digitally signed. JWTs can be signed using a secret (with the HMAC algorithm) or a public/private key pair using RSA.

JSON Web Tokens consist of three parts separated by dots (.), which are:

- Header
- Payload
- Signature

More information can be obtained from [https://jwt.io/introduction/](https://jwt.io/introduction/)



1. [/users/forgot](http://localhost:8000/users/forgot)   : Forgot Password : POST

This API call will enable the user to reset the password. Upon entering valid registered email id the API will call the mailing logic to end a mail to the user for password reset

The mail is generated from   [noreplygatormeetup@gmail.com](mailto:noreplygatormeetup@gmail.com) email id to the user . Upon clicking the URL in the mail the API calls   [reset/:token](http://localhost:8000/users/reset/:token)   API

Packages used   **Nodemailer**

**Command  ** npm install nodemailer --save

**Nodemailer**  is a module for Node.js applications to allow easy as cake email sending.

The API provides following feautures

- A single module with zero dependencies  code is easily auditable, as there are no dark corners
- Heavy focus on security, no-one likes RCE vulnerabilities
- Unicode support to use any characters, including emoji ??
- Windows support  you can install it with npm on Windows just like any other module, there are no compiled dependencies. Use it hassle free from Azure or from your Windows box
- Use HTML content, as well as plain text alternative
- Add Attachments to messages

5.  [users/reset/:token](http://localhost:8000/users/reset/:token)   : Reset Password   : GET

This API is used for password reset management .

Here the forgot URL is valid for 1 day or 24 hours which is set by using the expiry time

If the time elapses the password link click will throw an error as   Password reset link has been expired

Otherwise it generates an random token using the UUID API

In case the URL has been already used it generates a invalid token message

 ![](data:image/*;base64,)

6. [users/reset/:token](http://localhost:8000/users/reset/:token)   : Reset Password   : POST

This API gets called when the user clicks on the Forgot password link generated in the mail.It internally uses the UUID to keep track of the User details as a token and accepts the entered password.

So upon valid entry it calls Database call to update the user  details in the USERS table

Description

A universal unique identifier (UUID) is a standard of generating identifiers, standardized by the Open Software Foundation (OSF).

The intent of UUIDs is to be able to generate unique identifiers in a distributed system without central coordination point. Version 4 UUID is meant for generating UUIDs from truly-random or pseudo-random numbers.









Data Base

Users Table This table stores

| Column | Description |
| --- | --- |
| Name | It stores name of the user |
| Emailaddress | It stores the email address of user |
| Password | Encryped form of password storage |
| Location | Place of stay or preferred location of user |
| Hometown | Hometown of the user |
| Language | Primary language of user |
| DOB | Date of Birth of user in MM/DD/YYYY |
| Gender | Gender details |
| BIO | Some information regarding interests and general information of user |
